folder: Roosevelt Avenue & Union Street, Queens, NY
text:
Roosevelt Avenue, north side, between Union and Main Streets, Flushing, showing the old Armory of the 17th Separate Company, New York National Guard, erected in 1894. It is a brick and wood structure.
October 23, 1930
